I wanted to say a big thank you to the community for your help. I was able to get my agent up and running via a docker instance. A few items that I discovered:

1. Ensure the pre-requistes are installed on your VPC server. (pnpm, nvm, node etc.)
2. Install docker, and pull the latest repo which includes the dockerfile
3. Prior to building the docker container ensure that the following is done:
   a. copy your .env 
   b. create your character file
4. run pnpm docker ( this builds the docker container)
5. run pnpm build prior to running your character file, this builds the node project files.
6. Any change to the main /eliza files will require a new pnpm build from within the docker instance.
